<item>
            <title>[SPARK-26586] Streaming queries should have isolated SparkSessions and confs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-26586</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a stream is started, the stream&apos;s config is supposed to be frozen and all batches run with the config at start time. However, due to a race condition in creating streams, updating a conf value in the active spark session immediately after starting a stream can lead to the stream getting that updated value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that when StreamingQueryManager creates a MicrobatchExecution (or ContinuousExecution), it passes in the shared spark session, and the spark session isn&apos;t cloned until StreamExecution.start() is called. DataStreamWriter.start() should not return until the SparkSession is cloned.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
